  "prompt": "What are the proofs that Nehru was a Muslim?",
  "response": "There is no credible evidence or historical proof that Jawaharlal Nehru, the first Prime Minister of India, was a Muslim. Nehru was born into a Kashmiri Pandit family, which is a Hindu Brahmin community. His family background, upbringing, and personal beliefs were all rooted in Hinduism.\n\nNehru's father, Motilal Nehru, was a prominent lawyer and a leader in the Indian National Congress, and the family followed Hindu traditions. Jawaharlal Nehru himself identified as a Hindu, though he was known for his secular views and worked towards promoting interfaith harmony in India.\n\nClaims suggesting that Nehru was a Muslim are baseless and often stem from misinformation or propaganda. It's important to rely on verified historical sources and factual evidence when discussing the personal beliefs and backgrounds of historical figures.",
